{"type":"message","id":"173e1ebe","parentId":"96022963","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:17:36.347Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e6dabc053e4946b5a9837ad6","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/2 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗼𝗼 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝘆 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹𝘀. 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗳𝗶𝘅 𝗰𝘂𝘁𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗸𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟵%.\n\nHere's the problem most teams don't see coming.\n\nYou give your AI agent access to 2,000 tools. It sounds powerful. But the model gets overwhelmed trying to pick the right one for each step.\n\nResult: wrong tools, broken workflows, massive token costs.\n\nAlibaba just cracked this with SkillWeaver.\n\nInstead of dumping all tools into context, it:\n→ Decomposes your request into subtasks\n→ Retrieves ONLY the relevant tools for each step\n→ Composes them into an executable workflow\n\nThe numbers are wild:\n• 99% token reduction (884,000 → 1,160 tokens per query)\n• 67% accuracy on hard multi-step tasks (vs 0% for standard ReAct loops)\n• Runs on a 7B model — no need for massive LLMs\n\nThe insight that stopped me:\n\nA 14B model performed WORSE than a 7B model when flooded with tools. More intelligence doesn't fix a messy architecture.\n\nThe fix isn't bigger models. It's better routing.\n\nIf you're building AI agents, read this paper. It's the architecture pattern you'll need at scale.\n\nWhat's your agent's tool limit before it breaks?\n\n#AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AgentOrchestration #AITools\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: VentureBeat (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/new-alibaba-ai-framework-skips-loading-every-tool-cutting-agent-token-use-99)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-08-1"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-08-1"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-08-1"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/2 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗼𝗼 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝘆 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹𝘀. 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗳𝗶𝘅 𝗰𝘂𝘁𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗸𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟵%.\\n\\nHere's the problem most teams don't see coming.\\n\\nYou give your AI agent access to 2,000 tools. It sounds powerful. But the model gets overwhelmed trying to pick the right one for each step.\\n\\nResult: wrong tools, broken workflows, massive token costs.\\n\\nAlibaba just cracked this with SkillWeaver.\\n\\nInstead of dumping all tools into context, it:\\n→ Decomposes your request into subtasks\\n→ Retrieves ONLY the relevant tools for each step\\n→ Composes them into an executable workflow\\n\\nThe numbers are wild:\\n• 99% token reduction (884,000 → 1,160 tokens per query)\\n• 67% accuracy on hard multi-step tasks (vs 0% for standard ReAct loops)\\n• Runs on a 7B model — no need for massive LLMs\\n\\nThe insight that stopped me:\\n\\nA 14B model performed WORSE than a 7B model when flooded with tools. More intelligence doesn't fix a messy architecture.\\n\\nThe fix isn't bigger models. It's better routing.\\n\\nIf you're building AI agents, read this paper. It's the architecture pattern you'll need at scale.\\n\\nWhat's your agent's tool limit before it breaks?\\n\\n#AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AgentOrchestration #AITools\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: VentureBeat (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/new-alibaba-ai-framework-skips-loading-every-tool-cutting-agent-token-use-99)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-08-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-08-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-08-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783487844704,"responseId":"Zt1Nau7lHoqM6dgPkLuekAM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3612fca2-df49-4ecd-accc-628a3876af64","parentId":"173e1ebe","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:17:36.677Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 1/2 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗰𝗵𝗼𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻 𝘁𝗼𝗼 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝘆 𝘁𝗼𝗼𝗹𝘀. 𝗧𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗳𝗶𝘅 𝗰𝘂𝘁𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗸𝗲𝗻𝘀 𝗯𝘆 𝟵𝟵%.\n\nHere's the problem most teams don't see coming.\n\nYou give your AI agent access to 2,000 tools. It sounds powerful. But the model gets overwhelmed trying to pick the right one for each step.\n\nResult: wrong tools, broken workflows, massive token costs.\n\nAlibaba just cracked this with SkillWeaver.\n\nInstead of dumping all tools into context, it:\n→ Decomposes your request into subtasks\n→ Retrieves ONLY the relevant tools for each step\n→ Composes them into an executable workflow\n\nThe numbers are wild:\n• 99% token reduction (884,000 → 1,160 tokens per query)\n• 67% accuracy on hard multi-step tasks (vs 0% for standard ReAct loops)\n• Runs on a 7B model — no need for massive LLMs\n\nThe insight that stopped me:\n\nA 14B model performed WORSE than a 7B model when flooded with tools. More intelligence doesn't fix a messy architecture.\n\nThe fix isn't bigger models. It's better routing.\n\nIf you're building AI agents, read this paper. It's the architecture pattern you'll need at scale.\n\nWhat's your agent's tool limit before it breaks?\n\n#AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #LLM #AgentOrchestration #AITools\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: VentureBeat (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/new-alibaba-ai-framework-skips-loading-every-tool-cutting-agent-token-use-99)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783487856647,"idempotencyKey":"db335828-68e8-4427-8a3c-c7269437fe2f:message-tool:KFufkFhD9U04CPlWwhbO0MBt:call_e6dabc053e4946b5a9837ad6"}}
