{"type":"message","id":"ce7133af","parentId":"444c2c90","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:18:01.002Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_168b723ce4db44bdac1dc4fe","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/2 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗺𝗶𝗱𝗱𝗹𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗱𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗱𝗼𝗽𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻. 𝗔𝗻𝗱 𝗻𝗼𝗯𝗼𝗱𝘆'𝘀 𝘁𝗮𝗹𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝗶𝘁.\n\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable.\n\nMost companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\n\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\n\nMiddle managers are caught between:\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\n\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\n→ Tool selection and procurement\n→ Training and upskilling programs\n→ Change management across teams\n→ Security and compliance concerns\n→ Productivity expectations from above\n\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\n\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\n\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\n\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\n\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\n\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\n\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\n\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Harvard Business Review (https://hbr.org/2026/06/ai-adoption-is-overloading-your-middle-managers)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-08-2"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-08-2"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-08-2"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/2 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗺𝗶𝗱𝗱𝗹𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗱𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗱𝗼𝗽𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻. 𝗔𝗻𝗱 𝗻𝗼𝗯𝗼𝗱𝘆'𝘀 𝘁𝗮𝗹𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝗶𝘁.\\n\\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable.\\n\\nMost companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\\n\\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\\n\\nMiddle managers are caught between:\\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\\n\\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\\n→ Tool selection and procurement\\n→ Training and upskilling programs\\n→ Change management across teams\\n→ Security and compliance concerns\\n→ Productivity expectations from above\\n\\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\\n\\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\\n\\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\\n\\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\\n\\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\\n\\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\\n\\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\\n\\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Harvard Business Review (https://hbr.org/2026/06/ai-adoption-is-overloading-your-middle-managers)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-08-2\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-08-2\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-08-2\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783487856926,"responseId":"ct1NatzEK7-S6dgPqeLdoAI"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7fb73e6-b93b-434e-9fe9-2061cf89c14b","parentId":"ce7133af","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:18:01.238Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 2/2 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗺𝗶𝗱𝗱𝗹𝗲 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗱𝗿𝗼𝘄𝗻𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗶𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗱𝗼𝗽𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻. 𝗔𝗻𝗱 𝗻𝗼𝗯𝗼𝗱𝘆'𝘀 𝘁𝗮𝗹𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝗶𝘁.\n\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable.\n\nMost companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\n\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\n\nMiddle managers are caught between:\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\n\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\n→ Tool selection and procurement\n→ Training and upskilling programs\n→ Change management across teams\n→ Security and compliance concerns\n→ Productivity expectations from above\n\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\n\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\n\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\n\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\n\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\n\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\n\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\n\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Harvard Business Review (https://hbr.org/2026/06/ai-adoption-is-overloading-your-middle-managers)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1783487881210,"idempotencyKey":"db335